From 18f0d6f3b7357e6d4cbad339df9d95ec6f0b2f70 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Satoshi Teshiba <teshiba.satoshi@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 28 Feb 2026 12:00:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] crabbyavif: drop no_sanitize usage for Rust 1.91+

Rust 1.91 removed `feature(no_sanitize)` and the `no_sanitize` attribute.
Using `sanitize(...)` is still unstable and is blocked by Chromium's
`-Zallow-features` policy in this build.

Drop these crate-local CFI opt-out attributes to keep chromium-x11 building
with newer OE Rust toolchains.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific toolchain compatibility]
---
 third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/capi/io.rs         | 1 -
 third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/lib.rs             | 1 -
 third_party/crabbyavif/src/src/reformat/libyuv.rs | 2 --
 3 files changed, 4 deletions(-)

